Package: bola
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: automated BOLA/IDOR vulnerability detection via identity orchestration
 bola is a next-generation CLI tool for automated detection of Broken
 Object Level Authorization (BOLA/IDOR) vulnerabilities in modern web
 applications.
 .
 Unlike replay-only tools (Autorize, AuthMatrix), bola dynamically builds
 a resource ownership graph from live MITM proxy traffic or HAR file
 imports, then systematically tests cross-identity resource access with
 intelligent response comparison and confidence scoring.
 .
 Features include multi-identity session management with JWT/Cookie/Bearer
 auto-detection, transparent HTTP/HTTPS proxy, object ID extraction from
 URLs and JSON bodies, smart deduplication, and HackerOne-ready report
 generation.
 .
 Compiles to a single static binary with zero runtime dependencies.
